Chapter One
Korren
Itania time, 4:30 a.m. Korren hated waking up so early. Mainly because he was responsible for waking up the rest of the squad. He quietly got out of bed, put on his combat gear, strapped on his assault vest, packed his belongings from the storage cabinet, and carefully picked up a small special box. He shouldered his rifle, hung his helmet on a small hook on his belt. The helmet was equipped with a full set of gear, including a breathing apparatus, goggles, and other necessary items. After checking his ammunition pouch, he quietly left the barracks, his boots making crunching noises on the muddy and icy ground.
He took out a lighter from his jacket pocket and a cigarette from another pocket. After lighting the cigarette, he took a gentle puff and then opened the door. In the past week, he had to think hard just to wake up his subordinates. He no longer used the preset alarm, because half the time it didn't go off, and the speaker only emitted a faint hissing sound.
"Time to wake them up?" Korren turned around and saw Captain Nemich approaching.
"Yes," Korren answered.
"What are you planning to use this time?"
Korren hadn't even had time to answer when the door opened, and Harris, Krass, and a few others rushed out, already fully dressed and ready.
"Good morning," Krass said.
"What woke you up?" Korren asked.
"First of all, we really don't want to see what method you're going to use to wake everyone up today. Second, the first squad to get up can have priority for breakfast," said a soldier named Lavik. "You know how bad breakfast is."
Korren said, "You're right, Corporal Lavik." He reached out and pressed the switch. An ear-piercing alarm sounded throughout the barracks. He heard shouting and a rush of hurried footsteps inside.
"Good grief, Valturi," said Nemich. "I thought they should have learned by now to get up with you."
"My recruits at the training camp did that," Korren pointed to Harris, Krass, and Lavik. "But to be honest, their squad leader and platoon commander knew to get up before the soldiers."
A few seconds later, the rest of the squad ran out. They were all fully dressed and ready. Some of the new recruits looked sleepy, while others appeared very annoyed.
"Good morning, everyone," Korren said cheerfully.
"Excuse me, sir, why did you have to wake us up that way?" asked a squad member (corporal).
"Because those regular alarms are just junk. And Daybreak never sleeps in."
"Pack your personal belongings," Korren continued. As a lieutenant and deputy commander of the squad, he was responsible for assisting Captain Borlatin Xiao in supervising and leading the squad. "We won't be coming back. Sergeants and lieutenants, you and your squads have 15 minutes to do your final checks and bring along the rations needed for today."
The members of Exodus Squad dispersed quickly. They were part of the Second Assault Regiment of the Second Group Army. Before the merger, they were two independent squads: Cohort and Dagger. This was a elite squad, and Korren felt complex emotions about being promoted to lieutenant, for many reasons.
Korren and the first squad's squad leader, Nemychev, walked side by side along the brightly lit roads of the base, with the lights on both sides powered by generators. Most of the lights were red, which helped them avoid enemy bombers. To counter them, Daybreak has begun using "wildcat" tactics both in the air and on the ground.
"A new day, a new mission for the Hell's Vanguard." Nemychev chuckled dryly. "Where are they going to send us this time?"
"Some frontline base outside of Ianlos. We've been sent to support the ground assault." Korren said, taking a puff of his cigarette. He somewhat blamed Krass for getting him addicted to smoking, but thinking back on the past year, they had gone through countless battles, so he let it go and said nothing.
"It's terrible. The front lines are really tight," Nemychev muttered. "All the messages we get here are 'support the war, assist the Kurgen front,' but why not support the Hauran front?"
"Good point, brother." Korren said, flicking the cigarette butt into the mud. "We're going with the first armored squad, no need to walk. Captain Xiao should be there."
"Captain Xiao let us ride?" Nemic asked, surprised.
"Yes. To be honest, he's not as bad as I imagined. I mean, he's not great, but he's not讨厌 either."
Korren raised his thumb and index finger, pressing against his throat's microphone, while he moved his backpack onto his back. "All units of Exodus Squad, assemble at the West Zone Vehicle Yard after mission completion. We will depart with the First Armored Squad at 05:00."
Every few seconds, he received replies from the squad leaders. When they first came, Harris, Krass, and Ravek were all lower-ranking sergeants. Since basic training on Earth, the four of them have been close friends. Korren felt like he had known them for a long time, even though it had been less than two years. They were all squad leaders, but since a week ago, when the previous squad leader was shot by Daybreak snipers and retired due to injury, Krass started leading the Second Squad.
When they arrived at the vehicle yard, Korren and Nemic's eyes fell on about eight Cronos main battle tanks and four Stryker armored vehicles. Crew members were running around, ensuring their war machines were in working order. Korren quickly found Captain Borlatin Xiao in the crowd, who was talking to the commander of the armored squad. As they approached, Xiao looked at them and came forward, his usual indifferent face showing no emotion.
"Lieutenant Nemich... Captain Valturi..." he said, Korren slowed his pace, Captain Xiao looked at Korren's holster, then looked up. "Is the squad ready?"
